Ross River virus - Australia (New South Wales) 980109223432
Ross River virus - Australia (New South Wales) (02) 980112172830
Ross River virus infection - Australia
981231182153
Date: Sat, 6 Nov 1999
From: Chan Yow Cheong mailto:chanyowcheong@pacific.net.sg
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for Asia
Source: AAP ex The Australian 5 Nov 1999
http://www.news.com.au/

The West Australian Health Department has warned visitors and residents in
the south-west that they risk contracting Ross River virus.
The department's environmental health director Michael Jackson said today
conditions for breeding mosquitoes that transmit the virus were ideal
because of above average spring rainfalls and recent warmer temperatures.
He said the department's routine monitoring program had already shown the
virus to be present in coastal areas between Rockingham and Augusta.
"However, people throughout the south-west should be aware that both viruses
[and mosquitoes are not necessarily confined to the coast," Mr Jackson
said.
"Typical symptoms of Ross River virus infection vary considerably, but can
include painful or swollen joints, sore muscles, skin rashes, fever, chronic
fatigue and headaches."
He said there was no cure for the disease and no vaccines to prevent it.
People should avoid being outside when mosquitoes were most active, wear
loose clothing and keep insect repellent handy.
Mr Jackson said the Health Department would carry out mosquito control
programs where possible, but warned people to take personal protection
measures as well, because all mosquitoes could not be eliminated.
--
