<promed@promedmail.org>
[The West Australian Health Department may have the best surveillance
program in the world -- better than California's, which is a good one. In
collaboration, UWA (University of West Australia, which does most/all of the
work), the WA government, and local governments, collect a myriad of data:
numbers of mosquitoes, number of positive pools, antibody surveys (human),
sentinel chickens, temperature, precipitation, etc. They may soon be
tacking on GIS (geographical information systems).
So when WA says there is an alert, they mean business. - Mod.CHC
................................................chc/jw
